<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB04922</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT REQUIRING THE IMPLEMENTATION BY BRAND OWNERS OF MANAGEMENT PLANS THAT PROVIDE REFUND VALUES FOR CERTAIN BEVERAGE CONTAINERS</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : " Beverage Container Disposal Act "</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to mandate the creation and implementation of management plans for brand owners to recover their used beverage containers for reuse or recycling; Requires consumers to pay a deposit when purchasing a beverage in order to have them return the containers or to surrender them to a return site that will pay the refund value stated on the containers.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ROCAMORA, RAMON V.A. &quot;RAV&quot;</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2017-02-01</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Tambunting (000 2018-05-28)</td><td>2. Acosta-Alba (000 2018-05-29)</td><tr><td>3. Velasco-Catera (000 2018-07-24)</td><td>4. Nieto (000 2018-07-24)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITEE HEARINGS/ACTIONS:</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp1. Under deliberation by the Mother Committee on 2018-05-16</b><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON ECOLOGY ON 2017-02-08</td></tr></table>